.TH DOTS 7 "January 2026" "Eli Gundry" "Dotfiles Reference"
.SH NAME
dots \- keybindings and tips for Eli's dotfiles
.SH DESCRIPTION
Quick reference for keybindings and configuration across tmux, Ghostty, and other tools.
.SH TMUX
The prefix key is
.BR C-a
(Ctrl+a).
.SS Window Management
.TP
.B C-a c
New window (in current directory)
.TP
.B C-a x
Kill window (with confirmation)
.TP
.B C-a X
Kill window (no confirmation)
.TP
.B C-a K
Kill pane
.TP
.B C-a C-a
Switch to last window
.SS Moving Windows
.TP
.B tmux swap-window -s X -t Y
Swap window X with window Y
.SS Pane Splitting
.TP
.B C-a |
Split horizontally
.TP
.B C-a -
Split vertically
.TP
.B C-a _
Split vertically (small bottom pane)
.SS Pane Navigation
.TP
.B C-a h/j/k/l
Navigate panes (vim-style)
.SS Copy Mode
Enter copy mode with
.BR "C-a [" .
Uses vi keybindings.
.TP
.B v
Begin selection
.TP
.B y
Copy selection
.TP
.B C-a P
Paste buffer
.SS tmux-open Plugin (in copy mode)
.TP
.B o
Open selected URL/file with system open
.TP
.B C-o
Open selected file in $EDITOR
.TP
.B S
Search selected text in Google
.SS Miscellaneous
.TP
.B C-a R
Reload ~/.tmux.conf
.TP
.B C-a C-l
Clear scrollback history
.TP
.B C-a F3
Kill all sessions except current
.TP
.B C-a F5
Enable screensaver (10 min timeout)
.TP
.B C-a F6
Disable screensaver
.SH GHOSTTY
.SS Clicking Links with tmux Mouse Mode
When tmux mouse mode is enabled, use modifier keys to bypass tmux and click links:
.TP
.B Cmd+Click
Open link (macOS)
.TP
.B Shift+Cmd+Click
Open link (alternative)
.SH SSH
.SS macOS Keychain Integration
SSH keys are automatically unlocked via macOS Keychain. Configuration in
.IR ~/.ssh/config :
.PP
.RS
.nf
Host *
    AddKeysToAgent yes
    UseKeychain yes
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
.fi
.RE
.SS Adding Keys
Use the macOS built-in ssh-add (not Homebrew's) to store passphrases in Keychain:
.PP
.RS
.B /usr/bin/ssh-add --apple-use-keychain ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
.RE
.PP
Keys are loaded automatically when first needed.
.SH NEOVIM
Leader key is
.BR , " " (comma).
