.SH HOMEBREW
Packages are managed via a global Brewfile at
.IR ~/.Brewfile .
.SS Installing Packages
.TP
.B brew bundle add --global brew <package>
Install a package and add it to the global Brewfile
.TP
.B brew bundle --global
Install everything in the Brewfile
.SS Upgrading
.TP
.B brew upgrade
Upgrade all installed packages to latest versions
.SS Cleanup
.TP
.B brew bundle --global cleanup
Remove packages not listed in the Brewfile
.TP
.B brew bundle --global cleanup --force
Actually uninstall them (without --force it's a dry run)
